          %h3 Setting Up Foreman
          %p To create app groups, drag apps from finder into the white area that says "Drag apps here from finder to create new app groups."
          %p To add apps to a group, drag apps from finder onto the group's row.
          %p To remove apps from a group, mouse over an app and click the "x" button.

          

          %h3 Toggling Foreman
          %p <strong>&#x2318;&#x21E7;.</strong> (command+shift+period) is a global hotkey to show foreman.

          %h3 Activating an App Group
          %p Activating a group launches all the apps in that group. Use your mouse to hide or close the other apps:
          %ul
            %li <strong>click</strong> hide other apps
            %li <strong>shift+click</strong> close other apps

          %p You can also use the keyboard:
          %ul
            %li <strong>&#x2191;</strong> and <strong>&#x2193;</strong> select an app group
            %li <strong>&#x23ce;</strong> activate group and hide other apps
            %li <strong>&#x21e7; + &#x23ce;</strong> activate group and close other apps

          %p That's all there is to it! Foreman just does its thing and gets out of your way.            
        
